## Additional Observations

### Speed Insights Also Installed
The project also has Vercel Speed Insights configured:
- **Package**: `@vercel/speed-insights@2.0.0`
- **Import**: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/react';`
- **Usage**: `<SpeedInsights />` component added alongside Analytics

This provides comprehensive performance and usage monitoring for the application.

## Code Implementation

The implementation in `src/main.tsx` is clean and follows best practices:

```typescript
import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react';
import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/react';

ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('root')!).render(
  <React.StrictMode>
    <BrowserRouter>
      <Suspense fallback={<div />}> 
        <Routes>
          <Route path="/" element={<LoginPage />} />
          <Route path="/admin" element={<AdminPage />} />
          <Route path="/motorista" element={<DriverPage />} />
        </Routes>
      </Suspense>
    </BrowserRouter>
    <Analytics />
    <SpeedInsights />
  </React.StrictMode>,
);
```

## Next Steps for Activation

While the code implementation is complete, analytics will only collect data when:

1. The application is deployed to Vercel
2. Analytics is enabled in the Vercel dashboard for this project
3. The site receives traffic

## Conclusion

**No code changes were necessary**. The Vercel Web Analytics package is already properly installed and configured according to the latest official documentation. The implementation follows best practices for React/Vite applications and is production-ready.

